       A1200 ONLY...

                               Sound

        The Sound preferences editor is perhaps the simplest of all the
preferences programs. It simply allows you to control the operations of the
Amiga's DisplayBeep function that occurs when you do something wrong. Under
normal circumstances, the display will simply flash but you can assign a
sound to this function, either a simple beep or even a sampled sound. If
you're lucky enough to own a sound sampler, you could even assign a sample
of your own voice to the DisplayBeep function so that when you do something
wrong, the Amiga will politely (or very rudely) speak to you. The Sound
editor also gives you extensive control over the pitch of the sound, it's
volume and - in the case of a simple beep - the length of the sound.


